    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The Test conditions factor achieved level 2 against a required level 3; however, the assessment team judged that the single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol is consistent with regulatory precedent for this device class and that the literature review of analogous pedicle screw FEA studies provides sufficient corroborating evidence that the model framework generalises across plausible loading configurations. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; error < 10%). The package is accepted at Medium assurance level for submission in support of a 510(k) substantial equivalence argument.",
